  "prompt": "What is the best military school for troubled teens?",
  "response": "Choosing the best military school for troubled teens can depend on various factors, including the specific needs of the teenager, the school's programs, location, and the support provided to students. Here are some well-regarded military schools known for helping troubled teens:\n\n1. **Gonzaga College High School (Washington, D.C.)** - A college preparatory school with a strong discipline program, though not a \"troubled teen\" school specifically.\n\n2. **Citadel (Charleston, South Carolina)** - A military college that focuses on leadership and character development, offering various programs for youth.\n\n3. **New Mexico Military Institute (Roswell, New Mexico)** - Offers a structured environment and programs for both high school and junior college students.\n\n4. **Florida Preparatory Academy (Melbourne, Florida)** - A military-style academy that provides a structured environment for students who may benefit from more discipline.\n\n5. **Riverside Military Academy (Gainesville, Georgia)** - A private military academy for boys that focuses on leadership, education, and personal development.\n\n6. **Hargrave Military Academy (Chatham, Virginia)** - Offers a comprehensive program that includes academic and emotional support.\n\nIt's important for parents to conduct thorough research, visit campuses, and meet with staff to determine which program aligns best with their child's needs. Additionally, consulting with mental health professionals may provide valuable insights into the most suitable options.",
